ific Sunrise, Mosaic, El Dorado &amp; Nelson Hop Juice<br>• </span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><span>Stop Worrying and Have a Beer </span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>Czech Amber Lager</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-526\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b526\"><table id=\"section_0276fa542647330f6dbfeabfeb1d1490\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--26\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-12\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--33\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b533\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-529\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b447\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/45c6e9bf-5488-f4ee-8741-c0805eba3436.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/45c6e9bf-5488-f4ee-8741-c0805eba3436.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:298px;width:298px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-448\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b448\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span><span><span><span>🌺 Tropical Vacay sours<br>• </span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><span>Evil Twin Make it Fruity Spring Has Sprung </span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>Sour with Mango, Passionfruit &amp; Guava<br>• </span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><span>Feel the Rain Brothers Gosecolada</span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span> Pineapple Coconut Gose<br>• </span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><span>Commonwealth Conch Republic</span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span> Gose with Pink Guava, Lime, Papaya &amp; Passion Fruit</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td><td id=\"mceColumnId-532\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b530\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/44bd172c-c8f8-be24-dffd-8cb4cd4c87d5.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/44bd172c-c8f8-be24-dffd-8cb4cd4c87d5.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:298px;width:298px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-531\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b531\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span><span><span><span>💪🏻 Small but mighty<br>• </span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><span>Morning Recovery Sugar Free Watermelon </span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>is here</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b599\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-646\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b646\"><table><tbody><tr><td><span><span>Current Hot Crowler/Growler Fills</span></span><p><span><span><span>Final Gravity Supernova Hazy IPA</span></span></span></p><p><span><span><span>Benchtop Stanley’s Pilsner</span></span></span></p><p><span><span><span>Grimm Chance Encounter West Coast IPA</span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b645\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b579\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/0bb7f44d-5320-cb0e-3016-68ce0c4e4a72.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/0bb7f44d-5320-cb0e-3016-68ce0c4e4a72.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-580\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b580\"><table><tbody><tr><td><span>New wines in the door:</span><p><strong><span>Pomalo Wine Co Debit</span><span>: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>Pomalo means, roughly, relax / take it easy in Croatian, and this adorable bottle is absolutely giving that vibe. Take a vacation in your mind by popping open this refreshing and crushable white. Citrus, pear, and a hint of green apple plus a refreshing brininess and crisp acidity. Practicing organic, hand harvested, native yeast.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>Domaine de la Tonnellerie Sancerre</span><span>: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>This Sancerre had us at first sip! We're heading to a 13-hectare estate located in the Bue area of Sancerre where Domaine de la Tonnellerie has perfected the balance between mineral finesse, soft fruit and snappy citrus.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong>Mas de Boislauzon La Chaussynette: </strong><span><span><span><span>Siblings Christine and Daniel Chaussy (get it, Chaussynette?!) are the fifth generation to work their family’s domaine in Rhône with vineyards classified all the way up to the prestigious Chateauneuf-du-Pape appellation. Take a note from the label and share this playful bottle with friends and family. Fresh raspberries and cherries blend with rustic undertones of floral and pepper. Hand harvested, native yeast.</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span><span><span><span>Roots Wine Company Klee Pinot Noir: </span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>After graduating from college, Chris followed his parents from the midwest to Willamette where he planted a small vineyard. The name \"Roots\" is a tribute to his hometown of Racine, Wisconsin which translates to roots in French. Klee (pronounced \"clay\") Pinot Noir is a steal for the price with dark cherry and brambly raspberry accompanied by baking spice and dark chocolate. Organic, Practicing Biodynamic, Native Yeast, Unfined, Vegan.</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b416\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/9a65efc2-92ed-e515-7bab-21b10d1871dc.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/9a65efc2-92ed-e515-7bab-21b10d1871dc.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-415\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b415\"><table><tbody><tr><td>What we’re drinking this week:<p><span><span><span>Three years ago we included </span></span></span><strong><span><span><span>Avantis Estate Amygdalies Rose </span></span></span></strong><span><span><span>in our 6 Roses of Spring release. It became my warm-weather obsession and I secretly hoarded bottles just for myself. Yes, that factually does happen often - just ask Julie. As we've been shifting our wine selection for the impending warm days, it occurs to me that you all have also been crushing on Greek wines, specifically the Avantis Estate Historia and Mitravelas Red on Black. Me too, so I've decided to play fair and let everyone else try the infamous Amygdalies Rose.<br></span></span></span></p><p><span><span><span>Avantis has been quietly doing excellent work on the sun-drenched slopes of Evia, Greece for years. Made with Syrah, Amygdalies rests on the grape skins for one day to extract the most gorgeous pale salmon-pink hue. The nose is fresh and fruity &nbsp;- think strawberries, watermelon and a little squeeze of citrus. There's lovely red fruit through the mid-palate (hello, cherry and raspberry) and just enough heft to withstand your perfectly curated Mezze platter. Amygdalies means \"almond\" in Greek and, sure enough, there's a delicate nuttiness woven through the whole experience that makes it feel a little more complex than your average patio pour.<br></span></span></span></p><p><span><span><span>If you've yet to experience the joy of Greek wine stateside or otherwise, Amygdalies is a perfect gateway into why Greek wine deserves a permanent spot in your rotation. And, as added bonus points, Amygdalies hits the wallet nicely at $14.99 with an outdoor friendly screwcap. </span></span></span></p><p><em><span><span><span><span>This week’s writeup is brought to you by Beth.</span></span></span></span></em></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b98\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"https://arlbrew.us16.list-manage.com/track/click?u=be20bbfba341582993786f7f0&amp;id=6679e98f48&amp;e=01c6cdb4b7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SHOP OUR ENTIRE WINE SELECTION HERE</a></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]--><table><tbody><tr>\n<!--[if mso]>\n<td align=\"center\">\n<v:roundrect xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\"\nxmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\"\nhref=\"https://www.arlbrew.com/#!/Wine/c/48063559\"\nstyle=\"v-text-anchor:middle; width:395.3px; height:50.4px;\"\narcsize=\"0%\"\nstrokecolor=\"#b1dd8b\"\nstrokeweight=\"1px\"\nfillcolor=\"#b1dd8b\">\n<v:stroke dashstyle=\"solid\"/>\n<w:anchorlock />\n<center style=\"\ncolor: #000000;\ndisplay: block;\nfont-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif;\nfont-size: 16;\nfont-style: normal;\nfont-weight: bold;\nletter-spacing: 0px;\ntext-decoration: none;\ntext-align: center;\ndirection: ltr;\"\n>\nSHOP OUR ENTIRE WINE SELECTION HERE\n</center>\n</v:roundrect>\n</td>\n<![endif]-->\n</tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b508\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-452\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b452\"><table id=\"section_bb2271954ab7653a1c9ed6b77c0d3cc2\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--25\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-10\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--32\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b456\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-455\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b453\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/64983ef7-2e69-08b7-c6f4-87ecb6989a3b.jpeg\" width=\"534\" alt=\"breathe11x17in_2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tb